```sql
SELECT TOP 5 [RegionName], SUM([TRX(C4 Wk)]) AS TotalPrescriptions
FROM dbo.Reporting_BI_PrescriberOverview

ORDER BY TotalPrescriptions DESC
``` 

nl: I need to understand why some territories are underperforming - show me territories where we have good rep coverage and are doing lots of activities, but prescribers still aren't writing many prescriptions for our targeted products. Include the rep names so I can follow up.
sql:
-- This query identifies territories with good rep coverage and high activity levels, 
-- but low prescription rates for targeted products (Tirosint). 
-- It includes rep names for follow-up.

SELECT 
    [TerritoryId],
    [TerritoryName],
    [PrescriberName],
    COUNT([Calls4]) AS TotalCalls,
    SUM([TRX(C4 Wk)]) AS TotalPrescriptions
FROM 
    [dbo].[Reporting_BI_PrescriberOverview]
WHERE 
    [TirosintTargetFlag] = 'Y' -- Focus on prescribers targeted for Tirosint
GROUP BY 
    [TerritoryId], 
    [TerritoryName], 
    [PrescriberName]
HAVING 
    SUM([TRX(C4 Wk)]) < 10 -- Prescriptions are low
    AND COUNT([Calls4]) > 5 -- Good rep coverage with sufficient activity
ORDER BY 
    [TerritoryName]
